# TOOLS.local.md — your service notes

This file is **yours** and survives framework updates. `TOOLS.md` ships with
YodaCode and is overwritten when you update; this one never is. Keep anything
install-specific here: connected-service endpoints and quirks, camera names, SSH
host details, voice preferences — whatever you learn and want future-you to know.

When you connect a service, jot its endpoints and gotchas so you don't relearn them:

```
## ServiceName  (host: api.example.com)
- Endpoints: /users, /items, /orders
- Notes: rate-limited 100 req/min; use ?page= for pagination.
```
